<TITLE> Deputy secy accused of torturing wife to gain property </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 9 (bdnews24.com)A Kishoreganj court sent deputy secretary of the establishment ministry Abdul Jalil to jail on Wednesday in a dowry and repression case. Judge Md Robiul Hasan, of Kishoreganj district Women and Children Repression Prevention Tribunal, refused Jalil bail in the case that accuses him of physically and mentally torturing his wife to gain control of property inherited from her father. According to the case details, Jalil, 48, met his wife, Nusrat Jahan, when he was additional deputy commissioner in Kishoreganj. They married in Dec 2008. It is alleged Jalil received Tk 300,000 as dowry, which he used to repay loans, and later physically and mentally tortured his wife to gain property worth Tk 7,500,000. The case details also said Nusrat Jahan miscarried in March this year as a result of the physical torture. She filed a dowry and repression case with the Kishoreganj court on March 31. Jalil's family home is in Habiganj Sadar. bdnews
